The inflationary rates in America reach a new high; the business owners suffer greatly from the rising raw material costs and demand for exempting tariffs imposed on imports. Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhao Lijian also said China-U.S. economic cooperation will benefit each other mutually. There is no winner in trade wars that only cause harm for Beijing, Washington, and even the rest of world. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN reporter Aaron Liu will unwrap the rationales behind why the U.S. cannot afford the economic decoupling from China.